A real estate investment trust (REIT) is a type of company that owns a portfolio of income-producing properties that people can become shareholders in. Description: SEW-EURODRIVE is leader in power transmission products and services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: As a world leader in drive technology and a pioneer in drive-based automation, SEW-EURODRIVE has established a reputation for quickly solving the most difficult power transmission and motion control challenges. They introduced the gearmotor in 1931. In the 80 years since then, they have been bringing the best in drive technology to their customers. That commitment has led to a history of innovations — the first variable speed gearmotor, early development of electronic drives, some of the first successful efforts to decentralize control, and the first motor with energy-efficient copper rotors.   Exceptional solutions have made SEW-EURODRIVE the standard for drive performance and reliability in the United States since they first began working here in the early 1970s. Enthusiastic customer response to their variable speed gearmotors led us to open their first assembly center in Troy, Ohio, in 1975. Within a few short years, SEW was operating four additional regional assembly centers across the U.S. — in Bridgeport, NJ; Dallas, TX; Hayward, CA, and Lyman, SC. Today, they provide expert application assistance and products from their five regional assembly centers, more than 60 technical sales offices, and a nationwide distributor network.

Description: Neowin is a technology blog that specializes in tech reviews, news, and views.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Neowin.net is a technology site that actively focuses on Windows, Mac and Linux. Neowin runs under the slogan, "Where unprofessional journalism looks better." Neowin was started as a hobby in October 2000 by Marcel Klum and Steven Parker, known within the forums as "Redmak" and "Neobond" respectively, reporting news about the Windows XP alpha and beta release (then known as "Windows Codename Whistler"). Neowin has broken several stories, such as the leak of Windows 2000 source code onto the internet. Neowin focuses its attention on advanced computer users and technology enthusiasts of all kinds, although it is composed mainly of users of the Microsoft Windows operating system. It is worth noting, however, that it has active users of Linux- and Unix-based operating systems, including Mac OS X. Neowin also has its own Linux distribution called Shift Linux, which was previously based on Ubuntu, and is now based on Arch Linux. Development on Shift Linux was put on "indefinite hold" on 8 May 2009. The Neowin forums are Powered by Invision Power Board forum software. Neowin has an active technology forum consisting of 234,413 registered users (as of August 26, 2009) and over 8,809,121 posts. At its peak (February 28, 2008 at 04:20 GMT), Neowin's forum had as many as 11,724 users online simultaneously.

The company is registered in the US, based in Boston (with presence in Jerusalem), and is currently at the clinical stage. SynergyMed platform technology may be used as an alternative to surgery for the treatment of early-stage breast, head and neck, skin, and lung cancers for humans and also for the veterinary market. It may also be used for palliative care to relieve pain. The proven technology can locally ablate and destroy cancer tumors, precisely and effectively, without causing any damage to the surrounding healthy tissues. It is based on using specialized electromagnetic applicators which are placed around the region of interest. FDA approved nanoparticles are injected inside the tumor, which absorb the radiated electromagnetic energy efficiently, destroying the tumor without damaging the healthy tissue. The device is controlled through the company’s own developed algorithms which optimize the ablation process while precisely tracking temperature and measuring the administered treatment dose. The company has performed mice studies with breast cancer cell line, showing exceptional results, where the tumor disappeared within only a few days, leaving no scars or traces of cosmetic damage. It has also performed studies on superficial tumors in dogs with excellent results.  SynergyMed Devices Inc. has an experienced team with backgrounds from leading corporate and academic institutions. The company is currently seeking funding and strategic partnerships.

Full Description: Green Development LLC is the leading developer of large-scale renewable energy projects in Rhode Island, specializing in wind, solar, and battery storage. The company delivers significant energy savings to qualified organizations through the virtual net metering program. Founded in 2009, the company has built a portfolio of 135 MW of solar and wind projects, with plans to bring additional projects online in 2022. Green Development has played an important role in transforming and diversifying Rhode Island's energy portfolio. By providing a sustainable and reliable energy supply, the company helps generate in-state investment, increase energy security, and boost economic activity. Its renewable energy projects create local job opportunities, including construction, design, engineering, project management, corporate finance, and project maintenance. As the foremost developer of onshore wind energy in Rhode Island, Green Development's portfolio includes installations in Johnston, Coventry, Portsmouth, and North Kingstown, and the Port of Providence. Large solar energy sites are located in Richmond, West Greenwich, Hopkinton, Coventry, North Smithfield, and Johnston. Green Development LLC manages and owns renewable energy projects from start to finish, including planning and design, site development, project financing, construction, operation and maintenance, and asset management. Working with municipalities, quasi-public entities, schools, churches, housing authorities, and other nonprofit organizations, the company provides energy savings through the virtual net metering program. Farmers and landowners receive lease revenue for the small portion of land used for the project while preserving their farms. Green Development has expertise in financial and legislative requirements, supply chain, logistics, technological advancement, and project management. In-house experts are available to perform monitoring, routine maintenance, and repair projects. Since 2019, Solar Power World Online has recognized the company as a top solar contractor. In the recently published 2021 Top Solar Contractors list, Green Development is ranked #1 in installed capacity among 22 companies that completed projects in RI last year and in the top 24% of all U.S. solar developers, up 18 percentage points from the 2020 list.

It enables experts from various fields representing associations, financial planning professionals, academic institutions, think tanks, financial services industries, regulatory associations, and the federal government to contribute their knowledge and experience on critical personal finance issues affecting American families. The foundation provides funding, logistical support, and personal finance expertise to develop a variety of materials and programs, including the High School Financial Planning Program, the CashCourse college program, and the consumer-oriented Smart About Money public awareness campaign. Full Description: The usual process of learning bioinformatics requires the solution of computational problems of varying difficulty that are extracted from real challenges of molecular biology. The Rosalind website checks solutions to these problems automatically and provides students of all abilities with an intellectually stimulating way to learn key bioinformatics concepts and algorithms online at their own pace and independent of students' access to university resources.
